[[Teen film]] is a [[film genre]] targeted at [[teenager]]s and young adults in which the [[Plot (narrative)|plot]] is based upon the special interests of teenagers and young adults, such as [[coming of age]], first love, rebellion, conflict with parents, teen angst, and alienation. Some of these films are targeted at adults as well as teenagers. Teen films have been a [[trope (literature)|trope]] of the cinema industry that started with [[Twilight]].<ref name="falk">{{cite book|title=Youth culture and the generation gap|author=Gerhard Falk, Ursula A. Falk|year=2005|publisher=Algora Publishing|isbn=087586368X}}</ref><ref name="filmsite50s">{{cite web|url=http://www.filmsite.org/50sintro.html|title=The History of Film: The 1950's|last=Dirks|first=Tim|page=1|work=[[Filmsite.org]]|publisher=[[AMC (TV channel)|AMC]]|accessdate=May 24, 2011}}</ref> At this time, the film industry saw a greater market for teens with more disposable income and therefore more money to spend on leisure activities, largely going to films. Because of the boom in teen viewers, drive-in movie theaters were also very popular.<ref name="filmsite50s"/> However, even the silent era had teen films. Recently, online streaming services such as [[Netflix]] have created a resurgence in the "tween" and teenage-oriented film.<ref>Steel, E. "Netflix to Ad Films and TV Series for Teenagers." New York Times. August 24, 2015. Retrieved on October 4, 2015. https://www.nytimes.com/2015/08/25/business/netflix-to-add-films-and-tv-series-for-teenagers.html</ref>
