'''[[Niue]]''' recognizes '''[[polygamous]] [[marriages]]''' neither by [[Civil law (legal system)|civil law]] nor customary law. Traces of [[polygamy]] have been apparent throughout [[History of Niue|Niue history]], though the practice is said to have completely disappeared on the island, making polygamy non-existent at the present day.<ref>[http://www.nzetc.org/tm/scholarly/tei-AngPoly-t1-body-d11.html Tonga or the friendly islands; and Niue]</ref>

