[[File:Ethnic groups of Madagascar Map.png|thumb|right|200px|Distribution of Malagasy ethnic groups]]
The '''Zafisoro''' are a [[ethnic groups of Madagascar|Malagasy ethnic group]] inhabiting a portion of the southeastern coast of [[Madagascar]].{{sfn|Ogot|1992|p=}}  
The Zafisoro speak a dialect of the [[Malagasy language]], which is a branch of the [[Malayo-Polynesian languages|Malayo-Polynesian language group]] derived from the [[Barito languages]], spoken in southern [[Borneo]].{{sfn|Diagram Group|2013}}
